{
  "texts": [
    "However, increasing the data size to 100k has diminishing returns, especially in terms of BLEU and chrF++ scores, while it improves the COMET score.",
    "For inference, we use greedy generation by disabling the sampling options.",
    "We apply the prompt illustrated in Section 4.1.",
    "We use a batch size of 1, and set the generation max length to 1024 tokens.",
    "To evaluate our systems, we calculated BLEU (Papineni et al., 2002), chrF++ (Popović, 2017), as implemented in the sacreBLEU library foot_6 (Post, 2018)."
  ]
}